  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1631625691894-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1631625691894-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1631625691894-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1631625691894-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1631625691894-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631625826298-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631625826298-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631625826298-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631625826298-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631625826298-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice <strong>half</strong> the <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion wedge[s] </strong>finely and set aside for serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631625701572-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631625701572-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631625701572-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631625701572-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631625701572-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> lean beef mince </strong>to the dish with the <strong>red onion wedges </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a stir, breaking the <strong>lean beef mince </strong>up into rough, large pieces with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631625707935-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631625707935-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631625707935-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631625707935-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631625707935-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to the dish and stir it all up</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1631625713928-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1631625713928-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1631625713928-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1631625713928-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1631625713928-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained black beans</strong> to the dish with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[275ml]</span> [350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min – this is your <strong>oven-baked lean beef mince & black bean chilli</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1631625720358-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1631625720358-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1631625720358-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1631625720358-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1631625720358-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 20 min, chop your<strong> tortillas</strong> into quarters (keep them stacked for speedy chopping!)</p><p>Add the <strong>tortillas quarters</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through and lightly golden around the edges</p><p>Remove the lid from the chilli and return it to the oven, uncovered, for the final 5 min until the beef is cooked (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1646219304238-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1646219304238-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1646219304238-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1646219304238-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1646219304238-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, tear your<strong> coriander leaves</strong> all over the<strong> oven-baked lean beef mince & black bean chilli</strong> and garnish with the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>sliced red onion</strong></p><p>Dollop over your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and grate your <strong>cheddar</strong> <strong>cheese</strong> all over</p><p>Serve with the <strong>baked tortilla quarters</strong> to the side for scooping</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
